             was indicted for <rs id="t18280410-247-off1312" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280410-247-off1312" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-247-off1312" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280410-247-cd1313" type="crimeDate">8th of April</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-247-off1312 t18280410-247-cd1313"></join>, 1 watch, value 30s.; 2 seals, value 10s.; 1 ring, value 2s.; 1 watch-key, value 4s.; 1 cross, value 4s., and 1 watch-ribbon, value 1d., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18280410-247-victim1375" type="victimName">
                        John 
                        Miller
                     <interp inst="t18280410-247-victim1375" type="surname" value="Miller"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280410-247-victim1375" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280410-247-victim1375" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-247-off1312 t18280410-247-victim1375"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JOHN MILLER. I am a <rs id="t18280410-247-viclabel1314" type="occupation">seaman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-247-victim1375 t18280410-247-viclabel1314"></join>. I met the prisoner on the 8th of April, a little after two o'clock in the morning, in Ratcliff-highway. I had been out with a friend, but was quite sober; the prisoner was sitting down in the street; she accosted me, and asked me to go with her- we went to <placeName id="t18280410-247-crimeloc1315">No. 4, Angel-gardens</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-247-crimeloc1315" type="placeName" value="No. 4, Angel-gardens"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-247-crimeloc1315" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-247-off1312 t18280410-247-crimeloc1315"></join>; we went into a room; I asked her if she had any key, that I might lock the door - she produced one which would lock it outside, but not inside; we went to bed with the door latched; I was in bed about three hours - when I awoke she was gone: I went to my clothes, and missed my watch and 10s. in silver; my watch had been in my fob, and the silver in the left pocket of my trousers, which were in the chair at the foot of the bed - I am sure they were safe when I went to bed; I went down to the door, and saw a watchman - I asked him what place it was, and told him what I had lost. I saw the prisoner in custody in the afternoon; my ribbon and ring were found on her person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-247-person1376">
                  HENRY 
                  WADE
               <interp inst="t18280410-247-person1376" type="surname" value="WADE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-247-person1376" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-247-person1376" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. This watch was brought into our shop by the prisoner and another woman, to be pawned, and I stopped it; the prisoner said the person it belonged to was in a public-house; she went for him, and was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-247-person1377">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  BLABY
               <interp inst="t18280410-247-person1377" type="surname" value="BLABY"></interp>
